==English==

===Etymology===
from the context that to [[help]] with work, [[metaphorically]] a hand must be given; and thus a [[finger]] must be [[lift]]ed, being the bare [[minimum]] that can [[constitute]] as help.

===Verb phrase===
'''to lift a finger'''  (lifts a finger, lifted a finger, lifting a finger)
# to [[assist]], make even a [[minute]] [[effort]], offer help, or [[participate]] (usually [[negative]])
#:''We do all the work, and they never '''lift a finger''' to help.''

